BAKER v. UNITED STATES. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Eighth Circuit. December 21, 1914.) No. 4311. In Error to the District Court of the United: States for the Eastern'District of Oklahoma. James C. Denton, of Muskogee, Okl., for plaintiff in error. D. H. Linebaugh, U. S. Atty., of Atoka, Okl., for the United States.

Before SANBORN, ADAMS, and SMITH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Reversed, without costs to either party in this court, upon, the confession of error and consent of defendant in error, and cause remanded, with directions to sustain demurrer to indictment.
